1. Prompt Engineering Example

Prompt

Explain the role of inventory management in large construction projects and identify three common risks that poor inventory control can create.

⸻

AI Response (Original)

Inventory management is the process of tracking materials used in a construction project. It helps ensure materials are available when needed. If inventory is not managed well, it may lead to delays or increased costs.

⸻

Evaluation

Strengths:
	•	Provides a basic explanation of inventory management.
	•	Correctly identifies that poor management can lead to delays and higher costs.

Weaknesses:
	•	The response lacks detailed explanation.
	•	It does not include real-world construction examples.
	•	The risks are not clearly structured.

⸻

Improved Version

Inventory management plays a critical role in large construction projects by ensuring that materials are available when required without creating excessive stock.

Poor inventory control can create several risks:
	1.	Project Delays
If key materials such as HVAC ducting or electrical components are unavailable, installation work can halt until materials arrive.
	2.	Cost Overruns
Urgent procurement or expedited shipping can significantly increase project costs.
	3.	Material Waste or Obsolescence
Improper stock tracking can lead to unused materials aging in storage or becoming obsolete.

Effective inventory management systems use forecasting, cycle counting, and real-time tracking to reduce these risks.

