5. Logical Reasoning Evaluation Example

Prompt

A company maintains an inventory of 1,000 units. Weekly demand is 200 units and replenishment takes two weeks.

Is the company at risk of stockout?

⸻

Analysis

Weekly demand = 200 units
Lead time = 2 weeks

Demand during lead time:

200 × 2 = 400 units

If the company places an order when stock falls below 400 units, it may experience a stockout before replenishment arrives.

⸻

Conclusion

The company should maintain a reorder point above 400 units to prevent supply disruption.

Safety stock may also be required depending on demand variability.

